Section 1:
2 RELATING TO CRIMINAL COMPETENCY; PROVIDING FOR A METROPOLITAN
3 COURT TO RETAIN JURISDICTION OF A CASE IN WHICH THE QUESTION
4 OF A DEFENDANT'S COMPETENCY IS RAISED UNLESS THE METROPOLITAN
5 COURT DETERMINES THAT THE DEFENDANT IS NOT COMPETENT TO STAND
6 TRIAL; DECLARING AN EMERGENCY.
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
9 SECTION 1. Section 31-9-1 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1988,
10 Chapter 107, Section 1 and Laws 1988, Chapter 108, Section 1,
11 as amended) is amended to read:
12 "31-9-1. DETERMINATION OF COMPETENCY--RAISING THE
13 ISSUE.--
14 A. When a party or the court raises a question as
15 to a defendant's competency to stand trial in a criminal
16 case, the proceeding shall be suspended until the issue is
17 determined.
18 B. Unless the case is dismissed upon motion of a
19 party or through diversion, if the question of a defendant's
20 competency is raised in a court other than a district court
21 or metropolitan court, the case shall be transferred to the
22 district court; provided that if the question of a
23 defendant's competency is raised in a metropolitan court and
24 the court determines that the defendant is not competent to
25 stand trial, the case shall be transferred to the district SB 2
Page 1
1 court."
2 SECTION 2. EMERGENCY.--It is necessary for the public
3 peace, health and safety that this act take effect
4 immediately. SB 2
